zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr#99785.body:
### Describe the bug

The problem is that the `spi_shell.c` macro `RUN_FN_ON_SPI_DEVICE` is incorrectly including SPI child nodes because it only checks if a node is "on the SPI bus" (`DT_ON_BUS(node_id, spi)`), which is true for children of SPI devices.

The issue came in with Zephyr v4.3.0. It was no issue in v4.2.1.

### Regression

- [ ] This is a regression.

### Steps to reproduce

Add Multi Function Device including GPIO controller sub-device to device tree:
```
&spi1 {
	pinctrl-0 = <&spi1_nss_pa4 &spi1_sck_pa1
		     &spi1_miso_pa6 &spi1_mosi_pe15>;
	pinctrl-names = "default";
	status = "okay";

	ad559x: ad559x@0 {
		compatible = "adi,ad559x";
		reg = <0>;
		reset-gpios = <&gpiob 9 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>;
		spi-max-frequency = <2000000>;
		status = "okay";

		ad559x_gpios: gpio-controller {
			compatible = "adi,ad559x-gpio";
			gpio-controller;
			#gpio-cells = <2>;
