### Summary

After we encountered that our gpio callbacks didn't get called, we figured that the STM32 EXTI driver in `zephyr/drivers/interrupt_controller/intc_gpio_stm32.c` doesn't seem to support `CONFIG_SOC_SERIES_STM32N6X` yet.

We found a solution for now (see below) but would highly appreciate official support, ideally even with a back port to 4.3.0, if possible.

### Describe the solution you'd like

We manage to make it work by the following change:

```
void stm32_exti_set_line_src_port(gpio_pin_t line, uint32_t port)
{
	uint32_t ll_line = stm32_exti_linenum_to_src_cfg_line(line);

#if defined(CONFIG_SOC_SERIES_STM32L0X) && defined(LL_SYSCFG_EXTI_PORTH)
	/*
	 * Ports F and G are not present on some STM32L0 parts, so
	 * for these parts port H external interrupt should be enabled
	 * by writing value 0x5 instead of 0x7.
	 */
	if (port == STM32_PORTH) {
		port = LL_SYSCFG_EXTI_PORTH;
	}
#elif defined(CONFIG_SOC_SERIES_STM32N6X)
	switch (port)
	{
		case STM32_PORTA: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTA; break;
		case STM32_PORTB: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTB; break;
		case STM32_PORTC: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTC; break;
		case STM32_PORTD: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTD; break;
		case STM32_PORTE: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTE; break;
		case STM32_PORTF: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTF; break;
		case STM32_PORTG: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTG; break;
		case STM32_PORTH: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTH; break;
		case STM32_PORTN: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTN; break;
		case STM32_PORTO: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTO; break;
		case STM32_PORTP: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTP; break;
		case STM32_PORTQ: port = LL_EXTI_EXTI_PORTQ; break;
		default: __ASSERT_NO_MSG(!"INVALID GPIO PORT"); break;
	}
#endif

```

