zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr#101236.body:
### Describe the bug

Conventionally, if we want to disable a boolean property, we will use `/delete-property/` as tag before that certain field inside the overlay dts file. Inside mimxrt1180_evk.dtsi, `zephyr,random-mac-address` is set for each switch port:
```
// mimxrt1180_evk.dtsi, line 97
&switch_port0 {
	zephyr,random-mac-address;
	pinctrl-0 = <&eth0_default>;
	pinctrl-names = "default";
	phy-handle = <&phy0>;
	phy-connection-type = "rmii";
	status = "okay";
};
```
After adding `/delete-property/` before `zephyr,random-mac-address` and adding `local-mac-address` field inside the overlay dts, 
```
// mimxrt1180_evk_mimxrt1189_cm33.overlay
&switch_port0 {
    /delete-property/ zephyr,random-mac-address;
    local-mac-address = [00 00 00 01 04 00];
};

&switch_port1 {
    /delete-property/ zephyr,random-mac-address;
    local-mac-address = [00 00 00 01 05 00];
};

&switch_port2 {
    /delete-property/ zephyr,random-mac-address;
    local-mac-address = [00 00 00 01 06 00];
};

&switch_port3 {
	/delete-property/ zephyr,random-mac-address;
    local-mac-address = [00 00 00 01 07 00];
};

/* Internal port */
&switch_port4 {
    /delete-property/ zephyr,random-mac-address;
};
```
the MAC address for the switch port is still random instead of the specific value assigned by `local-mac-address`.

