zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr#102980.body:
### Describe the bug

In coap.h, we have

> /**
>  * @brief Description of CoAP resource.
>  *
>  * CoAP servers often want to register resources, so that clients can act on
>  * them, by fetching their state or requesting updates to them.
>  */
> struct coap_resource {
> 	/** Which function to be called for each CoAP method */
> 	coap_method_t get, post, put, del, fetch, patch, ipatch;
> 	/** Notify function to call */
> 	coap_notify_t notify;
> 	/** Resource path */
> 	const char * const *path;
> 	/** User specific opaque data */
> 	void *user_data;
> 	/** List of resource observers */
> 	sys_slist_t observers;
> 	/** Resource age */
> 	int age;
> };

Specifically, the user_data field is supposed to be user specific opaque data.

However, in the call path of 
`coap_well_known_core_get() > coap_well_known_core_get_len() > format_resource()`

`resource->user_data` is assumed to be `struct coap_core_metadata *`. If user_data is set, you end up in `format_attributes()`, passing whatever was in user_data as `const char * const *attributes`.

### Regression

- [ ] This is a regression.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a CoAP server with at least one attribute, and well-known/core. 
2. In the well known core callback, call coap_well_known_core_get()
3. Include an int * as user data
4. Do a GET request to well-known/core

for example

static struct coap_resource nw_test_coap_resources[] = {
    {
        .get = nw_coap_well_known_core_get,
        .path = COAP_WELL_KNOWN_CORE_PATH,
    },
    {
        .get  = hello_get,
        .path = hello_path
    },
    {},
};

and

int nw_coap_well_known_core_get(struct coap_resource *resource, struct coap_packet *request, struct sockaddr *addr, socklen_t addr_len) {
    struct coap_packet response = {0};
    uint8_t data[NW_COAP_MAX_MSG_LEN] = {0};
    int wk_core_get_err = coap_well_known_core_get(resource, request, &response, data, NW_COAP_MAX_MSG_LEN);
    if (wk_core_get_err < 0) {
        LOG_ERR("coap_well_known_core_get returned %d", wk_core_get_err);
        return wk_core_get_err;
    }
    int *socket_ptr = (int *)resource->user_data;
    int bound_socket = *socket_ptr;
    return zsock_sendto(
        bound_socket,
        response.data, response.offset,
        0,
        addr, addr_len
    );
}

